# Tic Tac Toe Game

This is a simple implementation of the classic Tic Tac Toe game using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. It provides a responsive and intuitive interface for users to play the game in their web browsers.

---

## Features

- **Responsive Design**: The game interface is designed to be responsive, ensuring optimal display on various screen sizes and devices.
- **Game Logic**: Implements the core logic of Tic Tac Toe, allowing players to take turns marking cells and determining the winner based on predefined win patterns.
- **Win Detection**: Automatically detects winning combinations and displays a message announcing the winner when a player achieves victory.
- **Draw Detection**: Recognizes when the game ends in a draw if all cells are filled without a winner.
- **Reset Functionality**: Provides options to reset the game either by clicking a dedicated reset button or starting a new game.

---

## How to Play

1. Open the Tic Tac Toe Game in your web browser.
2. Click on any available cell in the game board to place your mark (`O` or `X`).
3. Alternate turns with your opponent until one player achieves a winning combination or all cells are filled.
4. If a player wins or the game ends in a draw, a message will be displayed, and you can choose to start a new game or reset the current one.

---

## Technologies Used

- **HTML**: Provides the structure and content of the game interface.
- **CSS**: Defines the styles and layout of the game interface for an enhanced user experience.
- **JavaScript**: Implements the game logic, including player actions, win detection, and game reset functionality.

